      "content": "i get that, i'm not asking for generalizations or stereotypes. i'm literally looking for the data points that researchers use in sociology. like, if you look at raw FBI or census stats, there are certain disparities in arrest/conviction rates across different demographics. can u just outline what those statistical trends are without making a judgment on them? i need to know what the actual numbers show for my literature review.",
